description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Adult Mental Health PARTNER Team – Studdert Kennedy House&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Complex Discharge Facilitator &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Band 6&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;30 Hours per week – Permanent&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you an experienced, committed and dynamic registered practitioner; Social Worker or Mental Health Nurse (RMN) who wants to use their skills to make a difference?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Can you work effectively with those we care for, their families, clinicians, staff and other stakeholders to deliver exceptional quality care that changes people’s lives?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We’re searching for qualified, experienced registered practitioners for the established role of complex discharge facilitator within the PARTNER repatriation service based at Studdert Kennedy House in Worcester City Centre. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The PARTNER team provide care coordination and lead on the effective facilitation of discharges from high dependency rehabilitation units to high quality services that are as close to home as possible for people with complex mental health needs and their families, and where possible facilitating repatriation back to Worcestershire to a least restrictive environment as soon as clinically appropriate.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Applicants must be forward thinking, innovative, compassionate, creative and be willing to travel throughout England and Wales. The role is to work with people who use services and providers of their care to ensure a timely and smooth transition from hospital into community based services.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;About you&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will be passionate about making a difference to people’s lives. You will be responsible for undertaking assessments, designing bespoke care packages and procuring services for some of the most vulnerable people we are responsible for, many of whom will have complex and ongoing needs.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Personally, you will be skilled in liaising with independent providers, statutory and non-statutory services, skilled in interacting and working effectively with people who use our services, their families and carer’s, staff and stakeholders from all backgrounds.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Working automatously but part of a small team, you will make decisions that change lives every single day.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;About us&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The PARTNER service (Pro-active Repatriation through Negotiation Education and Recovery Service) support early and successful discharge of patients from high dependency rehabilitation units into community settings. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The service provides Care Coordination to provide momentum, challenge and additional capacity to support Social Workers in development and of packages of support to enable a successful transition into the community in supported or independent living or residential care, allowing them to recover in county.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We offer the opportunity for progression, excellent training including a thorough induction, linked to your role and professional development plans.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; You will receive professional supervision alongside weekly team reflective discussions and be working in a small team of motivated, dedicated and friendly colleagues.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The service operates from 9am-5pm, Monday to Friday (excluding bank holidays).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For an informal chat please contact Faith Robinson-Wain &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;faith.robinson-wain@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; 01905 734559&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;All staff whatever their role, level or responsibility will be encouraged and supported to do their job well and to improve their job.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Making Every Day Better for patients, staff, service users and carers is the responsibility of all of us and we want to embed a culture within the organisation that encourages and supports the drive to improve what we do.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
